sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: aiiA
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:description: autoinducer inactivation enzyme from Bacillus; hydrolyzes acetyl homoserine lactone
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance:
AF196486 from Bacillus sp. 240B1 putative metallohydrolase (aiiA) gene.
Dong,Y.H., Xu,J.L., Li,X.Z. and Zhang,L.H.: AiiA, an enzyme that inactivates the acylhomoserine lactone quorum-sensing signal and attenuates the virulence of Erwinia
carotovora, Proc. Natl. Acad. Sci. U.S.A. 97 (7), 3526-3531 (2000).
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Coding region for the autoinducer inactivation enzyme A (aiiA) LVA tagged. The gene was originally isolated from Bacillus sp. 240B1 and it encodes an enzyme that catalyzes the degradation of N-acyl homoserine lactones (AHLs)--quorum sensing autoinducers.

BBa_C0060 insert contains open reading frame (nucleotides 49-801) of the GeneBank sequence AF196486 followed by the LVA tag and two double stop codons inserted in the BioBrick prefix and suffix flanking regions. The original stop codon was TAG and in the present sequence it was substituted by TAATAA.

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0012
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableProvenance: Derived from the TE terminator of T7 bacteriophage between Genes 1.3 and 1.4 <genbank>V01146</genbank>.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcription terminator for the E.coli RNA polymerase.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableNotes:
Suggested by Sri Kosuri and Drew Endy as a high efficiency terminator. The 5' end cutoff was placed immediately after the TAA stop codon and the 3' end cutoff was placed just prior to the RBS of Gene 1.4 (before AAGGAG).

Use anywhere transcription should be stopped when the gene of interest is upstream of this terminator.
sbol:ComponentDefinition.dc:creator: Reshma Shetty

sbol:ComponentDefinition.dcterms:title: BBa_B0010
sbol:ComponentDefinition.sbh:mutableDescription: Transcriptional terminator consisting of a 64 bp stem-loop.
